/*
 * Non-secure (TF-M) variant.
 *
 * NOTE on retained RAM: this build does NOT carve a retained_mem region above
 * sram0_ns. Measured on silicon, a region carved above sram0_ns is outside the
 * kernel's MPU coverage and the non-secure app faults (MPU Data Access
 * Violation) when it touches it - the accessible window tracks sram0_ns's top
 * exactly. Instead the sample stores its retained state in a __noinit variable
 * inside sram0_ns (CONFIG_APP_RETAINED_NOINIT=y), which is MPU-covered, and the
 * secure RAM-control service keeps the RAM retained across System OFF.
 *
 * So there is nothing to add to the device tree here; sram0_ns keeps its full
 * board-default size. The TF-M service Kconfigs live in the matching .conf.
 */

/ {
};
